title: Grateful Dead Live at Hampton Coliseum on 1988-03-28

description:
Set 1

Feel Like A Stranger-> Franklin's Tower, Box Of Rain, When Push Comes To Shove, Walkin' Blues, It Must Have Been The Roses, When I Paint My Masterpiece, Bird Song, The Music Never Stopped

Set 2

Touch Of Grey, Women Are Smarter, Ship of Fools, Truckin'-> Drums-> Jam-> The Other One-> Stella Blue-> Throwing Stones-> Not Fade Away, E: The Mighty Quinn

reviews.review_text:
Spring 88 was pretty great it was gonna be hard to top the prior two nights' fireworks but this was still quite a solid show in its own right...1st set had a couple decent moments; you got a Phil tune, Roses, some pretty far out jamming in Birdsong and Music Never Stopped to set break. 

2nd Set was a little thin but Ship Of Fools and Truckin are solid. And I got berated for walking out of a Quinn encore. RIP Mike Cetrullo.
